President Joe Biden and President Jair Bolsonaro of Brazil recently met to emphasize the strategic significance of the relationship between the two countries. Amidst various global challenges such as the conflict in Ukraine, climate change, and pandemic recovery, the partnership between the United States and Brazil plays a crucial role in addressing the climate crisis and promoting peace. Both leaders committed to continuing their collaboration on trade and commercial matters, including the US's support for Brazil's OECD candidacy. They also discussed the importance of working together to promote sustainable development in the Amazon Basin by significantly reducing deforestation. Additionally, the leaders agreed to coordinate closely at the UN Security Council regarding Russia's invasion of Ukraine and to support democratic renewal.